						<summary>

						<p>Stone (No. IV) set up in the Vishaharēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Siṁgaṇa II A.D. 1228.</p>						

						<p>This damaged inscription referring to Siṁgaṇadeva is dated Śaka year 1150, Sarvadhāri, Chaitra, su. [15], Monday corresponding to A.D. 1228, March 20, Monday.</p>						

						<p>It praises the deity called Paṁḍaragenātha or Paṁḍaraṁga. Describes the king's <hi rend="italic">sarvādhikāri</hi> Āriya Malliseṭṭi, his son whose name is lost, Baṁdaṇikeya Bammidēva and the Thousand <hi rend="italic">Mahājanas</hi> of Piriya-Keṟavur. Seems to record a gift (details lost) made in favour of the deity by <hi rend="italic">Daṇṇāyaka</hi> Bāchaya into the hands of the divine Brahmarāsi.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
